shifts are actually pretty easy 

so for example when we have

section .data 
    num db 2

section .text 
    global _start   

_start:
    mov al, [num] ; 
    shr al, 1 

what it will basically do is divide this value by 2 
because in asm we usually work with bits, we mostly write base-2 numbers

so when we shift right, we are basically moving all the bits to the right
and the leftmost bit will be filled with 0

even easier here: 0010 -> step: 1[because we do shr al, **1**] -> 0001 

But what if we want to use it as a checker of "odd or even" 
its actually pretty easy too
since we know that the lsb goes to the carry flag when we use shr we can just check if its 0 or 1
and then do a jc instruction 